 1.5^\\circ$). When 60% sky coverage is analysed, we find that the\ndeviations never exceed 3$\\sigma$. Finally, we present a simple data-driven\nmodel to generate non-Gaussian and anisotropic simulations of the synchrotron\npolarized emission. The simulations are fitted in order to match the spectral\nand statistical properties of the faintest 80% sky coverage of the data maps.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 19 Jan 2023 12:35:38 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 11 Apr 2023 08:41:50 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-04-26"}
